crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detection of Linux variant of Winnti
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Silas Cutler (havex [@] chronicle.security), Chronicle Security

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a Linux backdoor that exhibits multiple malicious behaviors. It performs system fingerprinting by gathering OS release information (from `/etc/redhat-release`, `/etc/centos-release`), MAC addresses (`/sys/class/net/`), and the system UUID via `/usr/sbin/dmidecode`. It establishes a reverse shell by forking and executing `/bin/sh`, using pseudo-terminals (`posix_openpt`) for communication, and hides its activity by unsetting the shell history file (`HISTFILE=/dev/null`). It also uses PID files (`/var/run/libudev.pid`) to ensure only a single instance is running, masquerading as a legitimate system service.
